cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of Interactive Theorem Provers and the creation of libraries of formal proofs. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning to data-mine electronic libraries of proofs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the challenge of re-using libraries by non-experts or across domains. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the development of a tool to interactively data-mine proof libraries. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of electronic libraries of proofs.
